data.value:
Open beta 4 is a feature-drop update specifically designed to bring several optimizations and improvements for Hondana Project. Back before the full release of Hondana Project, we talked about an Open Beta 3 update in Nobember this year. At the time, we learned that the update would bring several new features for Windows devices, including a brand new Fluid Design inspired by Windows 11, an Experimental Forums screen and more underhood tweaks. Now, the fourth Open Beta has gone live for Beta Testers.
➤ User Interface • Optimized UI icons with improved textures, by using a design inspired by brand-new Fluid Design from Windows 11 materials and uniting lights and layers.
➤ Forums • Added an Experimental Forums screen, so you now can send messages to other users in the program.
➤ Database • The database has been restructured, adding new tables, triggers and stored procedures that will provide new query functions for the final program.
(And more, but i have hungry... maybe other day)
